I like to write C that is portable to build
as well as run. To that end, all of my projects should build
with any C compiler `cc`
that supports the C99, C11 or C23 standard. They have no other development
dependencies: no need for `pkgconfig`, or the presence of headers or libraries
beyond those that come included with a minimal version of the target operating system
(e.g. `libc` on Unix).

I test all projects
with [`gcc`][2], [`clang`][3], [`tcc`][4], [`cproc`][1], and
[`cl.exe`][6]---and most will even build with [`chibicc`][5].

